Ini-Parser

Ini::Parser provides simple parser to .ini files. Syntax which is supported:

    [section name]
    key1 = value
    "key2" = value
    key2 = "value"
    key3 = "multi
    line
    value"

    [section2]
    [section3 name]
    key4 = value4
    "key name = with equal" = value5

    !import = somefile.ini

    [section4]
    key5 = value5
    key6 = "${section1.key2} ${key7} ${section5.key8}"
    key7 = value7
    [section5]
    key8 = value8

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

Or just:
    cpan Ini::Parser

:)

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Ini::Parser

You can also look for information at:

    Ini::Parser home & source code
        https://github.com/mysz/ini-parser

    Issue tracker (report bugs here)
        https://github.com/mysz/ini-parser/issues

